$ dot (Graphviz)
@ dot

Dot is a → tools/Graphviz/dot/language[language] used by → tools/Graphviz to *describe directed or undirected graphs*.

Some examples of the usage of dot can be found → tools/Graphviz/examples[here].

The file extension of dot files is either `.dot` or `.gv` of which the latter is preferred because `.dot` is also used by
→ Microsoft/Office/Word[Microsoft Word].

sa:
  dot has some similarities with the → https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PIC_(markup_language)[PIC markup language].
